        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>WeatherBug Tip 
          of the Month</b></font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Pollen Forecasts</b></font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">As spring arrives, 
          so do high pollen counts in many areas of the United States. If you 
          or a member of your family is an allergy-sufferer, make sure to check 
          your WeatherBug four-day allergy forecast before leaving the house.</font></p>
        <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">To get to your allergy 
          forecast, click on Main Menu within your WeatherBug full view display. 
          Next, click on Pollen Forecast. A page containing your local four-day 
          pollen forecast will be launched. Ward off allergy attacks by being 
          prepared with WeatherBug!</font></p>
